EXPLAINATION:


A* Formula: f(n) = g(n) + h(n)
●	g(n) = cost from start to current node
●	h(n) = heuristic (estimated cost to goal) - Manhattan distance
●	f(n) = total estimated cost

Steps:
1.	Add start node to open list
2.	While open list not empty:
○	Pick node with lowest f value
○	If it's the goal → done
○	Move to closed list
○	Check all neighbors
○	Calculate f, g, h for each
○	Add to open list if better path found
3.	Backtrack from goal to start using parent pointers
 

